The [[steam locomotive]]s of '''kkStB Class 97''' were [[0-6-0T]] [[tank engines]] operated by the [[Imperial Royal Austrian State Railways]] (''kaiserlich-königliche österreichische Staatsbahnen''), or k.k.StB, for duties on secondary routes (''Nebenbahnen'') and branch lines (''Lokalbahnen''). They were built by the [[Lokomotivfabrik der StEG|works]] of the [[Imperial Royal Privileged Austrian State Railway Company]] (StEG) at Vienna between 1878 and 1911.
[[File:ÖBB 0-6-0T 97.274side.JPG|thumb|left|ÖBB 0-6-0T 97.273 at the [http://www.eisenbahnmuseum-heizhaus.com/ Vienna Railway Museum Heizhaus]]]

